This paper deals with the topic of biometric authentication using touchscreens, which falls under the category of computer security (cs.CR). The paper also involves the use of machine learning techniques such as recurrent neural networks and dynamic time warping, which are commonly used in computer vision (cs.CV) and machine learning (cs.LG) research. Additionally, the paper focuses on the human-computer interaction aspect of the authentication process, which could be categorized under human-computer interaction (cs.HC) or multimedia (cs.MM).
